33
00:03:27,185 --> 00:03:30,188
At least that's what he tells the girls,
eh, Neils?

34
00:03:30,355 --> 00:03:32,441
The name's Bender. Atomic physics.

35
00:03:32,524 --> 00:03:34,568
NEILSON: And you are?
SOL: Am I late?

36
00:03:34,651 --> 00:03:37,571
BENDER: Yes, Mr. Sol.
SOL: Oh, good. Hi.

37
00:03:38,447 --> 00:03:41,116
SOL: Sol. Richard Sol.
MARTIN: The burden of genius.

38
00:03:41,199 --> 00:03:43,577
- There he is.
- So many supplicants, and so little time.

39
00:03:43,619 --> 00:03:45,287
- Mr. Sol.
- How are you, sir?

40
00:03:45,370 --> 00:03:47,080
MARTIN: Bender.
BENDER: Nice to see you.

41
00:03:47,164 --> 00:03:49,917
BENDER: Congratulations, Mr. Hansen.
MARTIN: Thank you.

42
00:03:50,042 --> 00:03:51,752
I'll take another.

43
00:03:53,003 --> 00:03:54,129
Excuse me?

44
00:03:54,212 --> 00:03:56,465
MARTIN: Pardon me.
I assumed you were the waiter.

45
00:03:56,548 --> 00:03:59,217
BENDER: Play nice.
SOL: Nice is not Hansen's strong suit.

46
00:03:59,301 --> 00:04:00,636
MARTIN: Honest mistake.

47
00:04:00,719 --> 00:04:02,679
<i>Well, Martin Hansen. </i>

48
00:04:03,847 --> 00:04:05,557
